    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nIf a `foo.txt` help file is open and later closed or reverted externally (e.g. via `git checkout`), it shows this error:\n\n```\nError in FileType Autocommands for \"*\"..function <SNR>1_LoadFTPlugin[20]..script /usr/local/share/nvim/runtime/ftplugin/help.lua:\nE5113: Lua chunk: /usr/local/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/treesitter.lua:223: Index out of bounds\nstack traceback:\n\t[C]: in function 'nvim_buf_get_text'\n\t/usr/local/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/treesitter.lua:223: in function 'get_node_text'\n\t/usr/local/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/treesitter/query.lua:554: in function 'handler'\n\t/usr/local/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/treesitter/query.lua:878: in function '_match_predicates'\n\t/usr/local/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/treesitter/query.lua:1122: in function '(for generator)'\n\t/usr/local/share/nvim/runtime/ftplugin/help.lua:88: in main chunk\n```\n\ncc @yochem \n\n### Expected behavior\n\nHandle this scenario quietly, user does not need to see a stacktrace.",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "I'm not able to reproduce yet... Would a `nvim_buf_is_loaded` check on the current buffer work?\n\nE.g.:\n\n```diff\n\n+  local buf = vim.api.nvim_get_current_buf()\n+  if not vim.api.nvim_buf_is_loaded(buf) then\n+    return\n+  end\n   for _, match, metadata in query:iter_matches(root, buf, 0, -1) do\n```\n\n(the stack trace points at the \"runnables\" code. They both run iter_matches where the problem occurs. Both need to be fixed)",
