            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": ">  Easiest option is to put the parser:parse() call closer to the iter_matches code. Maybe that helps.\n\nHmm, they're already very close together, and the parser is deliberately not created inside the local context. But since parsing a parsed tree is a no-op, it should not hurt to put another defensive `parser:parse()` right before it (and another before the second `iter_matches`) -- with a comment of course.\n\nAt least it's worth a try to see if that has any effect.",
