            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "I've created a PR for the \"retry-approach\": #36592. @justinmk could you check if that fixes it. The retry mechanism can also be removed and changed to a single function call (`pcall`'d or not).\n\n> But since parsing a parsed tree is a no-op, it should not hurt to put another defensive parser:parse() right before it (and another before the second iter_matches) -- with a comment of course.\n\nThanks for the additional information! Then it's definitely fine to just call `:parse()` twice. Let's see if that resolves the issue.",
